    "level": 1
  },
  {
    "type": "callout",
    "text": "Haematemesis: Vomiting of fresh (bright red) or altered (coffee ground) blood.\nMelaena: Passage of loose, black, tarry sticky stools with deep offensive smell."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Both are typical manifestations of upper GI bleeding (bleeding from a site up to the transverse colon). Symptoms of blood loss such as fainting or postural dizziness may precede the appearance of haematemesis or melaena."
  },
